<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
Previously recorded only for Argentina (type locality) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.18348/opzool.2016.2.155" author="Olah, J" journalOrPublisher="More phenomics and less genomics! Opuscula Zoologica Budapest" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="155 - 171" refId="B51" refString="Olah, J, 2016. New species and records of Trichoptera collected by Mr. A.G. Duff. More phenomics and less genomics! Opuscula Zoologica Budapest 47: 155 - 171, DOI: https://doi.org/10.18348/opzool.2016.2.155" title="New species and records of Trichoptera collected by Mr. A. G. Duff." url="https://doi.org/10.18348/opzool.2016.2.155" volume="47" year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Oláh">Olah</normalizedToken>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). This study extends the known distribution of this species and provides the first record for Brazil. This disjunct distribution may be the result of omission errors, the article describing the species is difficult to access and the illustration provided lacks details. In order to avoid future the errors, omission we provide an illustration richer in details.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
